content.detailedDescription: I was working on my work inside my home when i wanted to check if it was overcast outside (it was common march to rain in fontana). i look to the left and i see a hovering object shaped similarly to a blimp. yet, there was something odd about this object. it had no reflection of light whatsoever, and was black and dull in color. it was located southward, and appeared to be circling very slowly around a place in san bernardino county. it was very visible, so i decided to grab my phone and take pictures of it. i first i doubted it was a ufo since it occurred during the daytime, but as i watched it i began to suspect. it lasted for approximately 10 minutes, yet after seven i went to look for my telescope to take a closer look. after an unsuccessful attempt to locate it. i went back to check if the ufo was still there, but it was gone. several hours later, i decided to report the incident
content.summary: A black, dull hovering object was seen circling around a certain place in san bernardino county

sighting 2 - @~6:15 am on 3.15.18 i was heading eastbound on garfield rd. to work. i was looking for activity due to the first sighting. surprisingly there they were again in and in larger numbers, roughly 11, and in the same area. i pulled in the same location as sighting #1. facing south i was prepared with my phone an managed to record 3 seperate videos. video 1 they are flying around in formation. video 2 they were moving rapdily around each other, slowing down then fast again, then moved around making different formations. i only recoginized one, it appeared to be the little dipper. video 3 after that they all came together and formed a v pattern and slowly headed north, until they reached garfield rd. then they sharply turned west and flew slowly above the road until they turned sharply again now heading south, flew slowly in that direction until they were out of sight. 

sighting 3  @~6:15 am on 3.17.18 i was heading eastbound on garfield rd. to see if i could observe further activity. when i arrived at the same location as sighting 1 & 2 i waited and snapped a couple photos of a suspected star, and a video of some lights in a flying v and changing shape. upon further review this may be a flock of birds but the spped seems to fast so i am not sure, but hopeful your team can find something if it is there.

i felt rattled and wondering what i just saw. i am still trying to figure out what it is and am hoping you may be able to eloborate.

content.detailedDescription: I deliver yachts on lake michigan. at dusk in the geographic center of lake michigan, the last weekend in july of 1989, i was with four other guys. we saw 5-6 bright aqua-colored discs under the water, moving in a zig-zag pattern. after 3-4 minutes, they came out of the water, hovering over the surface. all of a sudden they shot straight up into the sky, and disappeared in a blink of the eye. today,two of the guys admit what we saw, the other two will not. i have been on all the great lakes delivering boats for years, and lake michigan is the only lake on which i see weird stuff. (in 1996, closer to chicago, i saw white lights under the water that zig-zagged and hovered too.)
content.summary: 5 bright aqua discs below water in lake michigan; ascended straight up into sky.

content.detailedDescription: My brother,cousin,and me were coming back from jacks fork river it was a 2 and a half to 3 hour drive we were on hwy. 19 heading to herman mo. 20 to 30 miles from cuba i am driving come over the hill and right above us was the brightest light i have ever seen i stopped and it was above us i stopped then the light lite up the whole interior of the car i was so scared i have never felt terror like that  i woke up by brother he started to freak out he told me to get the hell out of there but the light was so bright i could not see to go foreword so i backed up and it fallowed us i stopped and tried to wake my cousin he would not wake up i was so scared i punched him in the face twice trying to wake him but did not move my brother and i were flipping out crying and more scared then we have ever been in our life(the light was so bright i could see the pores on my brother and cousins face and dust floating around)i tried to move foreword but it was right in front of me.The next thing you know me and my brother wake up on a dead end road in the middle of the woods,with no memory of what had happens to us we got to herman when the sun was coming up 5 to 6 hours after we left the river,(my cousin never woke up during this whole thing,and thinks me and my bro are crazy)for a couple of weeks i was having nightmares and me and my brother was talking about them when everything about the light came rushing back with all the feelings of terror we felt came rushing back we cried and relive everything all over again.We have no memory of the missing time.It has effected both of our lives in a negative way.
content.summary: 2 and a half hour drive from river to home my brother and cousin sleeping bright light above us  next we wake up 2 hrs later on dead end road

content.detailedDescription: We were traveling on the 15 freeway approaching the 60 and 10 freeways. we were looking for approaching jet airliners about to land at ontario airport as it was noticeably void of air traffic which directed my eyes further out in search of air traffic. i noticed in the northeast sky an odd form in the sky. my husband who was driving thought it was a blimp. i was not driving and thought it might be an advertising aerial display as continued closer to the object it appeared as solid and not a blimp or aerial display.  it appeared to be stationary in the sky with maybe a slight rotation as we were able to view the object at a different angle about this time an approaching airliner was observed about to land at ontario airport. the object was rectangular in form with no sharp edges and in our estimation it was at least as large/long as a large airliner. we were definitely amazed and curious at what we were seeing as we had never seen such a thing before. we left the 15 freeway and headed west on the 10 freeway when we lost our line of sight to the object. we are very sure that what we saw was solid and metallic and not shiny. it was not attached to anything it was stationary/hovering independently. attempts to take a photo were unsuccessful. wished we could have viewed longer.
content.summary: Viewed while traveling on the 15 near ontario airport mountains were behind sighting

content.detailedDescription: My brother and i were staying in a cabin on a lake in wayne maine.  we decided to do some night fishing so we went out on our kayaks and about 1230 or 1 o’clock in the morning all the sudden i saw this bright blue kind a greenish round looking object almost like a ball of energy at the tree line.  my brother was probably about 20 to 25 feet from me fishing in his kayak i yelled to him to look at the object we both saw it. it went around the entire lake right at the treeline.  we were probably about 30 yards from land so at the closest point to us it came about 30 yards away it was moving very fast and at that closest point when it came around i could hear leaves moving almost as if the wind from it made the leaves move.  at that point it scared us pretty good so we decided to paddle out of that area and back towards the cabin i actually fell out of my kayak from paddling so fast lost control. it was pretty scary my brother had to stop and help me get my things together and drag the kayak to the land about 30 yards two are right where i then got back into my kayak and paddle back to the cabin . we have both talked about it. where we were staying is in the middle of nowhere there’s no explanation for it was that we saw. i’ve never seen anything like it in my life. i know it was some type of ufo. to this day i can see it clear as if it just happened yesterday. only time ive ever seen anything like it.
content.summary: We we’re night fishing in the object went around the entire lake right at the tree line when i got closest to us could hear some type of leaf movement

content.detailedDescription: I was in my backyard, taking my dogs out and having a smoke. i noticed a flash in my peripheral vision and it drew my attention to that area of the sky. a couple of seconds later i saw another flash of light very close to where i had noticed the first one. maybe 10 seconds later a spherical shaped light slowly lit up, growing very bright, it seemed to shift colors slightly, like it took on a bluish tone. it then disappeared and another idententical sphere popped into view in a different part of the sky. i am unsure whether it was a another sphere or if it had just moved tens of miles in a split second. i see airplanes flying at night and meteorites all the time and knew this was not either of those. so i yelled into the house to my family to come and see. my 15 year old son came out and we watched the object hover, pulsate, grow very dim then intensely bright, change color and zip all over the sky for about 10-15 minutes. it was quite a show. sorry there is not video, i thought about going in and getting my phone but decided that it probably wouldn't have done any good because the object was so erratic and i had no idea how much longer it would be there. didn't want to miss it :p. there was some air traffic during this time. it looked to be standard commercial airliners. the last we saw of the object, it was "skipping" through the sky almost due west toward the gulf of mexico, near crystal river, fl.
content.flightPath: Stationary,Hovering then path,Straight-line path,Path with directional change,Path then hovering,Other
content.summary: Spherical object that would light up and move instantly from one position in the sky to another. hovered and pulsated a lot.

content.detailedDescription:
I was outside having a smoke admiring how blue the sky has been the last few days.  the sky was extremely blue with several white puffy clouds.   i was looking at the clouds when i noticed what i thought was a few pieces of small clouds moving fast in a v shape.  then i noticed they were not clouds and moving very smoothly in a v shaped formation.  i made out 6 semi triangular vehicles that resembled nothing i can compare it to. not like other ufo triangles i've seen described.  they had white bodies and what appeared to be black wings.  they were moving very, very fast and smoothly, unlike anything i've ever witnessed, with no sound at all.  they were very high up in the sky.  they glided together and moved perfectly together, extremely close to one another in the v shape but then they moved in a crooked line and back to the v shape, very smoothly and with perfect synchrony.  they flew directly overhead of us, made a turn and disappeared near the sun.  absolutely no sound, exhaust or movement besides the gliding. as they turned they were in a crooked line again and one of them changed shape by appearing to open, extend, rotate or adjust its wing, very hard to explain.  the way they were gliding was amazing. i lost sight when they got near the sun and they completely vanished.  i looked at the sky for another few minutes with no sign at all of them.  

i was wearing sunglasses and only saw white and black.  my boyfriend who also witnessed them saw gold/ white vehicle body and black wings and sparkles when they disappeared.  he was not wearing sunglasses. 

i felt very calm and a strange sense of excitement and  happy energy while witnessing it.  i feel it still as i write this and feel extremely lucky for some reason.  i was not scared.
content.summary: Six ufos flying in formation

content.detailedDescription:
Had been observing pleiades cluster through telescope (i am an amateur astronomer). i was taking a break from observing for a minute. i looked up at the sky (i believe i was considering what to point the telescope at next.) there seemed to be a black object moving against the background of stars. it was difficult to see, but it appeared to have a round outline. there seemed to be something like a crescent / semi-circular arc of cloudy white vapor near the forward edge of the object. the vapor was faintly illuminated. it was very difficult to judge size or distance to the object.
  i think my first thought was that the object was a cloud, but it was moving too fast, moving against what little wind there was, and had too regular a shape. i assumed that if i kept watching it, i'd be able to figure out what it was.
  it was moving too fast for me to train my telescope on it. (went from about 75 degrees above the horizon to about 15 degrees above the horizon in about 60 seconds.)
  the object appeared black or possibly transparent. almost like a lens that was distorting the images of the stars behind it. 
  the object appeared to hold a steady course and speed towards the north-west, moving much like a jet aircraft as far as i could tell. i moved my position by about ten feet while watching it to try to get a clearer view (there was one small, leafless tree obscuring). 
  i lost sight of the object when a car drove through the neighborhood and the car headlights (pointed almost straight at me) made it very difficult to see anything else. after the car left, i was not longer able to see the object which had been nearing the point where it would have been obscured by nearby houses and trees in any case.
  i saw a jet airliner a few moments later. the jet followed a path approximately perpendicular to that of the 'object' and about 35 degrees above the western horizon. i saw no indication that the jet was aware of the other object.
 the sight of the jet did give me a good reference for comparison. the object had seemed to move at approximately the same angular speed as the jet. if i assume that the object was moving at the same speed and at the same altitude (which i know is a lot to assume), then it would have been immense: a diameter at least 3 times the length of the 727 that passed through about 60 seconds later.
the sky was clear with excellent visibility. there were no clouds. the temperature was around 40 fahrenheit.
  i would speculate that the object might have been some kind of stealth aircraft...Possibly a b2? it was very difficult to judge exact shape and size: basically i observed a black object against a black background. my impression was that the object was very large and basically circular, but i suppose it is possible that it could have been 'wing-shaped.' also, the object made no discernible sound (most air-traffic in this area is audible), and the "crescent of white vapor" at the leading edge was puzzling. also, there were no conventional aircraft lights of any kind on the object. we are only 20 miles from a major airport and 5 miles from a small airport. there is considerable air traffic at that hour of the night. it seems very odd that even a military aircraft would operate without running lights of any kind in this area. if the object was a b2, then it should have been close enough for engine noise to be easily discernible. i heard nothing.
  after going into my house for a few minutes, i came back out to investigate several possible causes for what i saw (some kind of reflection? my own breath condensing somehow? some kind of spot light? a flock of birds somehow reflecting city lights? a drone? a blimp? a balloon?) none of these explanations seems to fit what i saw. it was too regular in outline for a flock of birds or a cloud. it was moving too fast for some of the other explanations, and it did not make any sound. also, a drone or other small object should have shown a much smaller angular size as it moved away from me. this object seemed to grow only slightly smaller as it moved towards the horizon, which would seem to indicate that it was at a considerable distance from me even when it was almost overhead.
  i was calm both during and after the incident. even though it is st. patrick's day, i have not consumed any alcohol in over 24 hours. my major reaction was to think, "i'm sure i can figure this out if i just think long enough." however, i have grown increasingly certain that no conventional explanation (that i can think of) completely fits what i observed. i wanted to post this while the memory is still fresh in my mind.
  to me the identity of object remains unknown.
content.summary: Black object with glowing white

content.detailedDescription: I was walking my dog over the fields, when she stopped and started shaking and her hair standing on end. about 30seconds later i heard a pulsating whizzing type of sound getting louder and louder, it seemed to be coming from directly above me getting very close, i then proceeded to feel the air rush down becoming very heavy to breath, as if the air around me had been compressed. as i looked around to see that i wasnt imagining this, i saw infront of me about 50yards away apart of the space in front of me was shimmering, i can only describe it as been like on star trek when part of a cloak fails. i walked over to the shimmering object and proceeded to try and touch it, as i did, for a split second i felt a cold hard surface, but before i could take a longer observation the whole thing whizzed up into the sky, the air that seemed to be compressed, whoosed up after the object as if the air was been sucked away. i felt very uneasy afterwards for a long time, and i still rarely go back over that field. i have never spoke about this before now, as i never realized that mufon existed. i did try to take some images, but like i said that object seemed to be cloaked and impossible for my camera to pick up the shimmering. i would like to know if anyone else has seen anything similar?
content.summary: I encountered what appeared to be a cloaked vessel

content.detailedDescription:
This just happened about 20 mins ago,so it is fresh and clear.

i was in the backyard having a smoke an looking up at the stars. i was looking at one and noticed a blurry line next to it. but the line was getting clear fast and all of a sudden it was about 7 to 8 lights in a straight line next to each other , not behind each other. i can't belive what i am seeing. i'm trying to figure out what they are.

then another group is suddenly there and mingles with the others then they also line up in a straight line. something comes out of the 3rd light, from the first group, that almost looked like a shooting star. it was fast left a slight trail and just quickly vanished. then they quickly seem to get in a v shape. appears to be kinda low and slow now. about as high as the airliners coming in landing nearby or lower. 
 
i can tell it / they are going to go right over head soon. so i run to get my daughter. i figured she is 15 and would be believed as a witness. someone else had to see this so i didn't sound crazy. so since it wasn't going very fast i took the chance. we run back out and it is almost right over head. as we look at it you can see there is more to it than just lights. it made no sound. it was definately something or things there. not birds or balloons,helicoptors or a jet. my daughter gets scared and runs inside after about 20 seconds. i had to watch it. it almost looked like that they were either one thing or so close together it looked like one solid thing. then another one of those shooting star things flys off from the front of it. 
as soon as that happened it suddenly sped up the lights in front start to disappear and then it just was gone.

i am stunned. can't workout what i just saw. i rush inside to hear what my daughter saw. she is sitting on the couch in a blanket shaking and scared. she said she thought it was low and one solid object with the lights either in or on it. it made no noise and  was not birds. i had to ask her if that could have been what we saw. she said there was no way it was birds.
i go back outside of course and start looking up again because i am trying to stay calm. she asks me to come back in and shows me on here phone what she thought it looked like. it was one of those v shaped "ufo's". she said that is close to what she saw. again i am stunned. it is not like her to go look something up. but what we saw, something so not normal, she wanted an answer. i don't have one for her. then she says why don't you report it.  i can't believe what we saw. and she is right, i should. and to see if you can tell us it wasn't what we think it was.
content.summary: White objects with dark bodys got in formation changed moved right over head, daughter saw also, scared her.

content.detailedDescription:

it was cigar shaped, metalic, traveling very fast and low to the ground at about 500 ft. it was completely silent, had no lights and disappeared behind a small hill beside the road.  i said to my wife we should see it cross the road in front of usin a second as the road was curving to the right.  when we rounded the curb the object had discppeared.

neither of us had seen anything like this before.  this object had no wings, exhaust, sound or anything that looked or flew like an airplane.

content.detailedDescription:
My father and his friend were out driving on the empty country side. they found some strange lights swirling, almost like a dance, around each other (very fast). both of them confused, decided to step out of the truck and watch the strange lights move. the three lights seemed to be communicating with different light sequences and colors. my father step up onto the trunk of the truck, grabbed a flash light- to then start blinking his flashlight in different patterns. the ufos stopped "dancing" (or moving at all) and flashed back in a white light with the same pattern each time. he continued this for about ten minutes. frightened and in shock, my father and his friend decided to go home. as soon as they stepped in the car- the ufos flashed them with a very harsh light which made the car stop working. the car would not start. they decided to step out of the car and flash the ufos once again. the ufos flashed them back and then all three flew in different directions, so fast if you were to blink it would have seemed like they vanished into thin air. once they flew away my father and his friend tried to start the car again. it worked as soon as the ufos flew away. they knew 100% this could not have been an airplane because of several reasons. 
1.  it was too fast.
2. the blue, yellow and red colors.
3. the "curly" movements.
content.summary: Found some strange lights swirling, almost like a dance, around each other
